The best thing they could do here Xan, is not so much make them random spawns but part of a spawn cycle.  Kill mob x, and 12 hours later mob y spawns.  Kill mob y, twelve hours later mob z spawns.  So on and so forth.  Or however long between spawns it would take to fill the current cycle.  The spawns should also be random, once the cycle completes.  By this I mean that mob x might spawn first one cycle, then be the third spawn on the next cycle.  This would mean that an uberguild wouldn't be able to wait for specific spawns as easily.  It might not prevent one guild from getting all the spawns, but it would inconvenience them and allow other guilds to hit high profile targets while they are busy in NToV, as you said.<br>
